
[1]scape-goat

   SCA'PE-GOAT, n. [escape and goat.] In the Jewish ritual, a goat which
   was brought to the door of the tabernacle, where the high priest laid
   his hands upon him, confessing the sins of the people, and putting them
   on the heat of the goat; after which the goat was sent into the
   wilderness, bearing the iniquities of the people. Lev. 14.
